-- Spain Rules Out More Health Austerity Measures, Mato Tells ABC
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-04-22T10:56:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/spain-rules-out-more-health-austerity-measures-mato-tells-abc.html
Spain  is ruling out the need for a
second wave of austerity measures to reduce the country’s public
health care costs, Health Minister Ana Mato said in an interview
with the  ABC  newspaper.  The Spanish health system’s “sustainability is
guaranteed” after the latest measures approved by the Cabinet
on April 20, Mato was quoted as saying, according to the paper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
